Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
check_tracks(25.10)                                        check_tracks(25.10)

Name
       check_tracks  - Checks a predefined set of tracks to verify their rout-
       ing track offset, direction, and grid

Syntax
       check_tracks

       [-help]

       [-direction {horiz | vert | H | V}]

       [-grid <spacing>]

       [-layer <layer_name>]

       [-mask <mask_name>]

       [-offset <string>]

       [-origin {design | core | D | C}]

       Checks a predefined set of tracks to verify their routing track offset,
       direction, and grid. It reports the following conditions in the Innovus
       log file:

              * Tracks whose STEP is smaller than the minimum  pitch  for  the
                designated layer.

              * The percentage of on-track pins and pins that are not accessi-
                ble (for regular routing).

              * Fully blocked pins and potential off-grid track pins (for spe-
                cial routing).

       Before running this command, complete the following steps:

              * Load a LEF file with the library and technology information.

              * Place the design.

Parameters
       -direction {horiz | vert | H | V}
              Specifies the direction of the tracks to check.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -grid <spacing>
              Specifies the track spacing.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each check_tracks parameter. For  a  detailed  de-
              scription  of the command and all of its parameters, use the man
              command:  man  check_tracks

       -layer <layer_name>
              Specifies the track layer.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -mask <mask_name>
              Specifies the mask name.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -offset <string>
              Specifies the track offset from the starting point.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -origin {design | core | D | C}
              Specifies the track starting point.

              Data_type: string, optional

Examples
              * The following command checks the tracks in the horizontal  di-
                rection on layer M3 with a grid spacing of 3.

                check_tracks -direction H -layer M3 -grid 3

                The following output displays on screen:

                Total  35  tracks  meet  specification: layer=Metal3 dir=horiz
                offset=0 grid=3

                Total 2622 tracks not hit under specified command line options

